STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Report of Foreign Issuer </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">Pursuant to Rule 13a-16 or 15d/16 of </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">November 2009 </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">AEGON N.V. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">AEGONplein 50 </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">2591 TV THE HAGUE </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The Netherlands </FONT></P>

<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A presentation of AEGON&#146;s results for the third quarter of 2009, intended solely for incorporation by
reference into AEGON&#146;s registration statement on Form F-3 (File No.&nbsp;333- 150786), is included as appendix and incorporated into this report by reference. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The presentation of AEGON&#146;s results for the third quarter of 2009, as included in the appendix, reflects some minor adjustments to the presentation of AEGON&#146;s results for the third quarter of
2009 as furnished to SEC under cover of a separate Report on Form 6-K on the date hereof. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Cautionary note regarding non-GAAP measures:
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This press release includes certain non-GAAP financial measures: net operating earnings, operating earnings before tax, underlying
earnings before tax, net underlying earnings and value of new business. The reconciliation of underlying earnings before tax and operating earnings before tax to the most comparable IFRS measures is provided on page 8. A reconciliation of (net)
underlying earnings to operating earnings before tax is provided on page 23. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Value of new business is not based on IFRS, which are used to
report AEGON&#146;s quarterly statements and should not be viewed as a substitute for IFRS financial measures. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">AEGON believes that these
non-GAAP measures, together with the IFRS information, provide a meaningful measure for the investment community to evaluate AEGON&#146;s business relative to the businesses of our peers. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24px;margin-bottom:0px"
ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">SIGNATURE </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Pursuant to the requirements of the Securities Exchange Act of
1934, the registrant has duly caused this report to be signed on its behalf by the undersigned, thereunto duly authorized. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">IGD</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">a</SUP></FONT><FONT

ratio increased further to 211% </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:24px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Statement Alex Wynaendts, CEO </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">AEGON&#146;s improved capital position, the strength of our franchise and return to profit in the third quarter are evidence that the actions we initiated a
year ago were the right ones at the right time. On November&nbsp;30 we will repay EUR 1 billion to the Dutch government, an important first step toward full repayment of the capital support AEGON received last year. We are pleased that our strong
capital position has enabled us to take this step while continuing to maintain a larger capital buffer, a necessary precaution in the current environment. We are also encouraged by the improved sales and net deposits for the quarter and the
continued confidence of our customers. Moreover, we have achieved our full-year cost savings target of EUR 150&nbsp;million and further reduced AEGON&#146;s risk to financial markets. AEGON today is in a strong position and we remain committed to
further executing our strategy to position our businesses for long-term growth and profitability. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>KEY PERFORMANCE INDICATORS

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">STRATEGIC HIGHLIGHTS AND SHORT-TERM PRIORITIES </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">AEGON has set out three long-term strategic priorities: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">1.</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">To reallocate capital toward businesses with higher growth and return prospects; </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">2.</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">To improve growth and returns from existing businesses; </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">3.</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">To manage AEGON as an international company. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">AEGON further aims to reduce its earnings sensitivity to financial markets to generate more stable earnings going forward. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="2"><B>Portfolio review </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">AEGON continues to assess its businesses to ensure they meet requirements in terms of earnings growth, cash
flow and return on capital potential. As a result of this portfolio review AEGON is running off its institutional spread-based and auto credit businesses in the US, its group risk business in the UK, and has sold its Taiwanese life insurance
operations. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Cost measures </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">AEGON made further progress in implementing cost saving measures and has achieved its 2009 target of EUR 150 million. Operating expenses for the first nine months of 2009 declined by 5%, excluding the impact of restructuring charges,
increased employee benefit plan expenses and currency effects. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Recently, AEGON announced that it will reorganize its Dutch sales
organization, which will result in an annual cost savings of EUR 15 million. This reorganization involves compulsory redundancies and will result in a charge of EUR 20 million. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Capital preservation </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">During Q3 2009, a further EUR 0.9 billion of capital was released
from AEGON&#146;s businesses, bringing the total for the first nine months of 2009 to EUR 2.5 billion and EUR 4.2 billion since the initiation of the capital preservation program in June 2008. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Capital&nbsp;&amp; risk management </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="2"><I>Excess capital </I></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="3%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="97%"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP
STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></SUP><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Excess capital above AA capital adequacy requirements amounted to EUR 4.8 billion, up from EUR 3.5 billion at the end of Q2 2009. In normal circumstances AEGON aims to maintain
an excess capital of EUR 1.5 to 2 billion. However, in the current environment AEGON aims to maintain a substantially larger capital buffer.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP
STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></SUP><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">De-risking and capital efficiency measures totaling EUR 0.9 billion and statutory earnings of EUR 0.4 billion further added to AEGON&#146;s excess capital position, partly offset
by rating migration in the United States of EUR 0.2 billion, impairment charges of EUR 0.2 billion and other items. AEGON has included in its Q3 2009 results the recently announced capital management transaction that releases approximately USD
650&nbsp;million of additional regulatory capital to its US operations.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP
STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></SUP><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">AEGON successfully completed a EUR 1 billion equity issue on August&nbsp;13, 2009. The proceeds of which will be used to repay one-third of the EUR 3 billion of core capital the
company secured last year through its largest shareholder, Vereniging AEGON and funded by the Dutch State. As announced, AEGON will repay this EUR 1 billion on November&nbsp;30.</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>IFRS core capital </I></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="3%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="97%"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP
STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></SUP><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">At the end of September 2009, core capital, excluding the revaluation reserves, totaled EUR 16.4 billion or 80% of the total capital base, well above AEGON&#146;s self-imposed
minimum target of 70%<I><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">7,8</SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"></FONT></I><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">.</FONT></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP
STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></SUP><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Core capital, including the revaluation reserve, amounted to EUR 14.6 billion, consisting of EUR 11.6 billion in shareholders&#146; equity and EUR 3 billion in convertible core
capital securities.</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" ALIGN="center">

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


 <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:24px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P
STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="3%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="97%"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP
STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></SUP><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">AEGON&#146;s revaluation reserves improved by a significant amount of EUR 3.3 billion, during Q3 2009 to a negative EUR 1.8 billion at September&nbsp;30, 2009. Approximately 85%
of the improvement of the revaluation reserves is related to the narrowing of credit spreads and approximately 15% is the result of lower risk-free interest rates. </FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">AEGON recently submitted a plan, through the Dutch Ministry of Finance, to the European Commission to
demonstrate that its businesses are fundamentally sound and viable. This plan is a requirement for all financial institutions that received state support during the financial crisis. The timing and outcome of this process have not been specified.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>Improved risk profile </I></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">To
reduce AEGON&#146;s sensitivity to financial markets, AEGON has substantially reduced its equity and credit market risk. In addition, AEGON lowered its long-term interest rate risk by selling the Taiwanese life insurance business. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>Equity market sensitivity </I></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">During Q3 2009,
AEGON further reduced exposure to equity markets by hedging 50% of the indirect equity exposure embedded in guarantees within its Dutch business, using futures and limiting future earnings volatility. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>Credit market sensitivity </I></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">As a result of
the decision to reduce sensitivity to financial markets, AEGON is running off its institutional spread-based business, reducing its exposure to credit risk. By the end of 2010, these balances will have decreased by approximately USD 20 billion,
freeing up approximately USD 0.8 billion of capital. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In order to fund these outflows, assets from the institutional spread-based business
have been transferred internally to other businesses in the United States in exchange for cash. As a result, the institutional spread-based business realizes a negative spread on these assets which negatively impacts underlying earnings. In the
first nine months of 2009, AEGON has reduced its institutional spread-based balances by USD 9 billion. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Following the compression of credit
spreads, AEGON has decided to reduce its exposure to credit derivatives, further reducing AEGON&#146;s earnings and capital volatility to financial markets. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Manage AEGON as an international company </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="3%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="97%"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP
STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></SUP><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">AEGON&#146;s new global asset management business formally started on October&nbsp;1, combining its international asset management operations in one international organization.
</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP
STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></SUP><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A European data center was opened in the United Kingdom, bringing together the data centers from the United Kingdom and the Netherlands, saving costs and significantly improving
efficiency.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP
STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></SUP><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">To further improve marketing effectiveness, AEGON Scottish Equitable will be rebranded solely as AEGON. Brand awareness in the United Kingdom has increased strongly since AEGON
became the lead partner of British tennis.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP
STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></SUP><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Leveraging on expertise in the United States and the United Kingdom, further progress has been made in developing variable annuity products. Product launches are planned in Q4
both in the Netherlands and Japan.</FONT></TD></TR>

<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Life and protection</FONT></P></TD>

<TD COLSPAN="1" NOWRAP VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="right" COLSPAN="1" VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">2,344</FONT></TD>
<TD COLSPAN="1" NOWRAP VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="right" COLSPAN="1" VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">4</FONT></TD>
<TD COLSPAN="1" NOWRAP VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


 <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">OPERATIONAL HIGHLIGHTS </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Underlying earnings before tax </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In Q3 2009, underlying earnings before tax amounted to EUR 351 million. Underlying earnings were impacted by de-risking measures implemented to counter the effects of the financial crisis. These measures
impacted Q3 earnings by approximately EUR 40 million. Underlying earnings before tax were also impacted by lower equity markets and by several exceptional items (EUR 66 million). Excluding exceptional items, underlying earnings would have been EUR
417&nbsp;million for the third quarter. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The exceptional items were: </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="3%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="97%"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP
STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></SUP><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Provisions related to a program to improve the consistency of customer records in the United Kingdom of EUR 43 million;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP
STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></SUP><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Accelerated amortization of deferred policy acquisition cost (DPAC) of EUR 23&nbsp;million in the fixed annuity business, as a result of the internal asset transfers related to
the run-off of the institutional spread-based business in the United States.</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Underlying earnings before tax in the Americas decreased 30% to USD 403&nbsp;million compared with Q3
2008, as a result of lower product spreads, reduced fees from lower asset balances, increased employee benefit plan expenses and accelerated DPAC in the fixed annuity business. Product spreads in the Institutional spread-based business have been
significantly reduced due to asset transfers to other US businesses in exchange for cash. In Q3 2008, the Americas results included DPAC charges related to variable annuities and unfavorable mortality experience for Life Reinsurance. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In the Netherlands, underlying earnings before tax increased to EUR 102&nbsp;million, or 38%, compared with Q3 2008, primarily the result of higher
investment income in the life and pensions businesses. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In the United Kingdom, underlying earnings before tax decreased compared to Q3 2008 to
a loss of GBP 11 million. This was mainly the result of an exceptional charge of GBP 38&nbsp;million related to a program to improve the consistency of customer records. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Underlying earnings before tax from Other countries totaled EUR 42 million. Excluding the results of AEGON&#146;s Taiwanese Life business, which was sold in Q2 2009, underlying earnings before tax were up
60%. This increase was mainly driven by improved results for CAM Vida, one of AEGON&#146;s Spanish bank partners, and the Life business in Central&nbsp;&amp; Eastern Europe (CEE). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Interest charges and other, included in underlying earnings before tax, represent holding expenses and amounted to a charge of EUR 69 million. The increase compared with Q3 2008 is mainly attributable to
higher interest expenses. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Fair value items </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In the Americas, fair value items showed an underperformance of USD 97&nbsp;million (EUR 76 million). The overperformance of fair value assets, total return annuities, credit derivatives and GMWB
guarantees, were more than offset by the result of AEGON&#146;s equity hedge program related to its retail variable annuity portfolio in the United States which amounted to a loss of USD 252&nbsp;million (EUR 184 million). In the Netherlands, fair
value items over-performed by EUR 39&nbsp;million due to the positive impact of movements in the fair value of guarantees and related hedges. Fair value items for the holding consist of three bonds issued by AEGON, which, together with related
hedges, are held at fair value through profit or loss. Further narrowing of AEGON&#146;s own credit spread during Q3 2009 resulted in a loss of EUR 27 million. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="85%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="13%"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" NOWRAP><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Page&nbsp;5&nbsp;of&nbsp;28</B></FONT></TD></TR>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


 <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:24px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P
STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Results on investments </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">During Q3 2009, AEGON recorded losses on investments totaling EUR 100 million. Trading gains on the bond portfolios in the Netherlands and the United Kingdom were more than offset by trading losses in the
Americas and depreciation of direct residential real estate investments in the Netherlands. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Impairment charges </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Net impairment charges decreased significantly compared with Q3 2008 to EUR 285 million. However, net impairments remained higher than AEGON&#146;s average
long-term impairment expectations. Impairments on US housing market related assets of EUR 74&nbsp;million were considerably lower compared with previous quarters. In the United Kingdom impairments increased to EUR 80&nbsp;million, related to
corporate credit investments. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Income tax </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The third quarter of 2009 included a tax gain of EUR 154&nbsp;million related to cross border intercompany reinsurance transactions between Ireland and the United States. These reinsurance transactions
are accounted for at fair value in both tax jurisdictions. While losses in the United States were taxed at 35%, gains in Ireland were taxed at 12.5%. The tax gains related to these internal transactions, totaling EUR 399&nbsp;million in the first
nine months of 2009, are a partial reversal of the EUR 490&nbsp;million of tax charges for the full year 2008. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Net income </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Net income increased to EUR 145&nbsp;million compared to a loss in Q3 2008, primarily the result of improved results of fair value items, lower impairment
charges and the reversal of prior year tax charges. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Commissions and expenses </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Operating expenses declined 2% in Q3 2009 compared with Q3 2008. Operating expenses for the first nine months of 2009 declined by 5%, excluding the impact of
restructuring charges, increased employee benefit plan expenses and currency effects. Total commissions and expenses in the first nine months increased primarily as a result of higher DPAC amortization in the Americas related to lower equity markets
in Q1 2009. Consistent with lower sales levels, fewer expenses were deferred and commissions decreased compared to the first three quarters of 2008. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="2"><B>New life sales </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Total new life sales were up 3% compared with Q2 2009 to EUR 484&nbsp;million as a result of higher single
premium sales. In the Americas, retail life sales increased by 11% as a result of strong term life sales and higher universal life sales, while in the Netherlands the increase in sales was driven by group pension contracts. In the United Kingdom,
sales declined, mainly as a result of the closure of the group risk business. In Central&nbsp;&amp; Eastern Europe (CEE), new life sales increased 21% compared to Q2 2009, while in Spain sales declined during the quarter. In Asia sales were level
with Q2 2009. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Deposits </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">Total gross deposits, excluding institutional guaranteed products, increased to EUR 6.8 billion, or 20% compared with Q2 2009. The increase was the result of strong pension and retail mutual fund deposits in the United States, higher
savings deposits in the Netherlands, new asset management contracts in the United Kingdom and higher mutual fund sales in China. As anticipated, gross deposits of fixed annuities were lower as crediting rates have been lowered, while variable
annuity deposits declined in both the Americas and the United Kingdom. Net deposits, excluding institutional guaranteed products, increased to EUR 2 billion, mainly due to the large increase in deposits and improved persistency in pensions and asset
management. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


 <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:24px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P
STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Value of new business </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Value of new business amounted to EUR 169&nbsp;million in Q3 2009, a decline of 7% compared with Q2 2009. VNB in the Netherlands increased as a result of higher sales volumes and improved margins, and in
the Americas, VNB increased slightly in local currency. However, these increases were more than offset by declines in the United Kingdom and Other countries, as well as currency effects. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Revenue-generating investments </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Revenue-generating investments increased to EUR 354 billion
during Q3 2009, an increase of 4% compared with Q2 2009. This is the result of a further rise in equity markets combined with narrowing credit spreads and slightly lower interest rate levels in addition to net inflows. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>SALES </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Individual Savings&nbsp;&amp; Retirement underlying earnings before tax increased to USD 104&nbsp;million, primarily due to extraordinary 2008 reserve strengthening and
accelerated DPAC amortization in the variable annuity business. The increased equity markets in Q3 2009 did not lead to a reserve release on the variable annuity book, but resulted in lowering AEGON&#146;s medium-term equity market return
assumptions to 8%, below the long-term assumption of 9%. Fixed annuity underlying earnings before tax were impacted by lower yields from higher than average cash balances and an exceptional DPAC charge of USD 31&nbsp;million, related to the internal
transfer of assets. Underlying earnings before tax in Q3 2009 were also impacted by USD 11&nbsp;million from increased employee benefit plan expenses;</FONT></TD></TR>

transferred to other portfolios in exchange for cash. The amortization consolidates to zero in aggregate, however, it was established to mirror a non-distressed market value transfer of the assets between portfolios.</FONT></TD></TR>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Net income </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Net income improved to USD 232&nbsp;million for Q3 2009 compared to a net loss of USD 578&nbsp;million for the comparable period last year. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The underperformance of fair value items of USD 97&nbsp;million is primarily the result of the negative impact of USD 252&nbsp;million related to a macro hedge. This hedge was implemented during Q2 2009
to reduce the sensitivity of AEGON&#146;s capital position to equity market movements within AEGON&#146;s retail variable annuity portfolio. These hedge instruments are carried at fair value through profit or loss. Most other fair value items
overperformed their expected returns. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Realized losses on investments amounted to USD 98&nbsp;million, resulting primarily from trading in the
bond portfolio. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


 <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:24px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P
STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Although net impairments were at their lowest level in five quarters, they continue to be above
AEGON&#146;s average long-term impairment expectations and totaled USD 287&nbsp;million, of which USD 117&nbsp;million was related to structured assets. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Net income also included a tax gain of USD 211&nbsp;million related to cross border intercompany reinsurance treaties. This gain is a partial reversal of previous tax charges of USD 718&nbsp;million on
these internal transactions in 2008. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Commissions and expenses </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Total commissions and expenses increased by 28% compared with Q3 2008 as a result of higher DAC amortization charges. Operating expenses were level with the third quarter last year. However, operating
expenses for the first nine months of 2009, excluding employee benefit plan costs and restructuring charges, decreased by 9%. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Sales and
deposits </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Total new life sales increased 10% to USD 202&nbsp;million compared with Q2 2009. Retail new life sales increased 11%, primarily
as a result of strong term life sales. This is the second quarter of growth after five consecutive quarters of declining retail life sales. Life reinsurance sales increased 4%, while activity in the BOLI/COLI market remained limited in the current
economic environment. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Sales of accident and health products declined by 8% compared with Q2 2009, due to the run-off of the auto credit
business. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In line with management expectations, fixed annuity deposits declined to USD 691&nbsp;million as a result of lower crediting rates
offered to customers. Variable annuity deposits declined to USD 912&nbsp;million, a strong result considering recent product repricing. Mutual fund sales increased substantially, mainly as a result of improved equity markets. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Pension deposits of USD 2.7 billion continue to be strong taking into account lower takeover balances due to lower equity markets compared to last year. As
a result of the decision to run-off the institutional spread-based balances, no new spread-based business is being sold. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Value of new
business </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Value of new business increased 2% over Q2 2009 to USD 92&nbsp;million as higher VNB from life, pensions and variable annuities
more than offset the decline in VNB from lower fixed annuity production. The internal rate of return improved over Q2 2009 to 12.1%. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="2"><B>Revenue-generating investments </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Revenue-generating investments for the Americas increased 5% during Q3 2009 to USD 310 billion,
as a decline in spread-based institutional balances was more than compensated by improvements of financial markets and continued net inflows. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="85%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="13%"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" NOWRAP><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Page&nbsp;10&nbsp;of&nbsp;28</B></FONT></TD></TR>

<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>

<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>

<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><B></B></FONT></SUP><FONT

<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B></B><B>Value of new business increased to EUR 51&nbsp;million, the result of higher margins and volumes</B></FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Underlying earnings before tax </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Underlying earnings before tax increased 38% to EUR 102&nbsp;million compared with Q3 2008. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="3%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="97%"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></SUP><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Underlying earnings before tax from Life&nbsp;&amp; Protection increased to EUR 70&nbsp;million as higher investment income in the Life business more than compensated for lower
underwriting results in Accident&nbsp;&amp; Health. Q3 2008 included costs for modifying unit-linked insurance products of EUR 28 million;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></SUP><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Continued fierce competition in the savings market and low short-term interest rates led the Savings business to report an underlying loss before tax of EUR 8
million;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></SUP><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Pensions&nbsp;&amp; Asset Management underlying earnings before tax increased to EUR 38 million. Higher investment income was partly offset by lower technical
results;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></SUP><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Underlying earnings before tax from Distribution decreased to EUR 3&nbsp;million due to a slowdown in the real estate and mortgage market;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></SUP><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Adverse claims experience in Fire and pressure on premiums in Motor resulted in an underlying loss before tax of EUR 2&nbsp;million for General Insurance.</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Net income </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Net income improved to EUR 74 million. Fair value items in Q3 2009 included a net benefit of EUR 41&nbsp;million, due to the positive impact of movements in the fair value of guarantees and related
hedges. Losses on investments amounted to EUR 34&nbsp;million as depreciation of AEGON&#146;s direct real estate portfolio was only partly offset by gains on bonds. Impairment charges have improved considerably over recent quarters. Impairments
during the quarter were mainly related to private equity investments. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Commissions and expenses </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Commissions and expenses decreased slightly compared with Q3 2008. Cost savings measures are being implemented and are on track to reach the 2009 target.
Operating expenses for the first nine months of 2009 decreased by 3% compared with last year. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Sales and deposits </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Pension sales totaling EUR 33&nbsp;million were strong, mainly as a result of several new contracts. The group pension market in the Netherlands, however,
proves to be volatile. Life sales were EUR 19&nbsp;million, level with Q2 2009. Of the new mortgage production, 70% was sold with a national mortgage guarantee (NHG). Gross deposits were up strongly compared with Q2 2009. Net deposits turned
positive as a result of the increased savings deposits. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Value of new business </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Higher sales volumes and margins in life, mortgages and pensions led to an increased value of new business of EUR 51 million. The improvement of the internal
rate of return was mainly driven by a shift in business mix. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Revenue-generating investments </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Compared to the end of Q2 2009, revenue-generating investments increased 6% to EUR 69.7 billion as a result of lower interest rates, improved credit spreads
and net inflows. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP

<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B></B><B>Underlying loss before tax of GPB 11&nbsp;million, mainly as a result of exceptional charges</B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP
STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><B></B></FONT></SUP><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><B></B></FONT>

<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B></B><B>Net deposits substantially increased as a result of several new asset management mandates</B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP
STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><B></B></FONT></SUP><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><B></B></FONT>
</FONT></B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Value of new business decreased to GBP 29&nbsp;million, mainly due to lower annuity margins</B></FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Underlying earnings before tax </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Underlying earnings before tax decreased compared with Q3 2008 to an underlying loss before tax of GBP 11&nbsp;million, mainly as a result of an exceptional charge of GBP 38&nbsp;million related to a
program to improve consistency of customer records. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="98%"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP
STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></SUP><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Underlying earnings before tax from Life&nbsp;&amp; Protection amounted to GBP 10&nbsp;million, in-line with the comparable period last year;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP
STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></SUP><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Pensions&nbsp;&amp; Asset Management recorded an underlying loss before tax of GBP 18&nbsp;million as growth of the business was more than offset by the exceptional charge of GBP
38&nbsp;million related to a program to improve consistency of customer records;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:4px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><FONT STYLE="font-family:ARIAL" SIZE="1"><SUP
STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"></FONT></SUP><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="1"></FONT></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Distribution experienced lower income due to difficult market conditions for mortgage and investment products, which resulted in an underlying loss before tax for the quarter of
GBP 3 million.</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Regarding the program to improve the quality and consistency of customer records and operational
effectiveness, an analysis of customer records is being conducted. This analysis is expected to be completed by the end of 2009. Two examples of issues identified which will be addressed during this program are: improving the quality of records to
enable AEGON to return money to former customers who have unclaimed assets, and rebating fund charges to customers who have overpaid. AEGON is determined to resolve these issues during this program. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Net income </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">AEGON reported a loss of GBP
33&nbsp;million in the United Kingdom in Q3 2009, primarily due to an underlying loss and higher impairment charges. Gains on investments totaled GBP 26&nbsp;million, including a GBP 14&nbsp;million gain on a derivative instrument for which hedge
accounting could no longer be applied. Impairments increased to GBP 70&nbsp;million, related to corporate credit investments. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Commissions
and expenses </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Total commissions and expenses increased 4% compared with Q3 2008, while operating expenses increased 9% as a result of
higher restructuring costs and a rise in risk and regulatory costs. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Sales and deposits </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">New life sales decreased by 2% to GBP 218&nbsp;million compared to Q2 2009 as increases in annuity and personal pensions sales were offset by lower group
pensions and employee benefit production. The latter is a result of the decision to close the group risk business. Gross deposits substantially increased over Q2 2009 to GBP 491&nbsp;million as a result of several new asset management mandates.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Value of new business </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Value
of new business in Q3 2009 declined to GBP 29&nbsp;million, primarily a result of lower margins on annuity products. The internal rate of return in the United Kingdom remained stable compared to Q2 2009 at 13.4%. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Revenue-generating investments </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">Revenue-generating investments increased 15% to GBP 54.2 billion, primarily as a result of a strong recovery in financial markets. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Underlying earnings before tax from Other countries remained level compared with the third quarter of last year and totaled EUR 42 million. However, excluding the results of Taiwan, underlying earnings

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Net income </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Other countries&#146; net income increased to EUR 31&nbsp;million mainly as a result of higher underlying earnings, higher gains on investments and lower impairments. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Commissions and expenses </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Commissions and
expenses, excluding Taiwan, decreased 5%, as higher commissions and operating expenses were more than offset by an increase in deferred expenses. Operating expenses increased due to continued growth of the business, while commissions also increased
as a result of a shift in business mix towards recurring premium business. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Sales and deposits </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Total new life sales of EUR 41&nbsp;million were lower compared with Q2 2009 as the lower production in Spain and China more than offset growth in the CEE.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="middle"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In Asia, new life sales were level with Q2 2009 and totaled EUR 6 million. Commissions on a certain product were lowered in China, impacting sales in the agency
channel.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>

consolidated in AEGON&#146;s accounts, amounted to EUR 9 million.</FONT></TD></TR>

<TD VALIGN="middle"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Sales of general insurance products in Hungary increased to EUR 6&nbsp;million in what continues to be a competitive market.</FONT></TD></TR>

<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="3"></TD></TR>

compared with Q2 2009 to EUR 736 million.</FONT></P></TD></TR>

STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Value of new business from Other countries in Q3 2009 totaled EUR 21&nbsp;million, a 38% decrease compared with Q2 2009. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The higher contribution from Variable Annuities Europe was more than offset by lower VNB from Spain. The contributions of CEE and Asia were level compared to Q2 2009 and in-line with sales. The internal
rate of return for Other countries remained at a high level. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Revenue-generating investments </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">During Q3 2009, revenue-generating investments increased 8% to EUR 11.7 billion compared with Q2 2009 as a result of market appreciation and net inflows.
